article.description: Matt Rafferty scored 18 points and grabbed a career-best 14 rebounds as Furman rolled to a 98-48 victory over Division II Hiwassee on Friday night.
article.headline: Furman rolls to 98-48 win over Division II Hiwassee
article.linkText: Furman rolls to 98-48 win over Division II Hiwassee
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- Matt Rafferty scored 18 points and grabbed a career-best 14 rebounds as Furman rolled to a 98-48 victory over Division II Hiwassee on Friday night. Rafferty made 8 of 11 field goals. Geoff Beans scored 14 points and made four 3-pointers for Furman (3-3). Kris Acox added 13 points and Daniel Fowler had 11 for the Paladins, who shot 57 percent from the floor, forced 20 turnovers, and outrebounded the Tigers 54-27. Ben Snider had 10 points to lead Hiwassee. The Tigers shot just 29 percent from the field, including 4 of 20 from 3-point range. The Paladins had a double-digit lead six minutes into the game and led 47-25 at the break. Beans' 3-pointer gave Furman a 62-30 lead with about 15 minutes remaining. It was the first meeting between the schools.
